summary: Day 8 - Ahoy from Mr Briney 3:17 am, stay posted for future me please! Thanks for your patience! [image description: a digital...
caption:
Day 8 - Ahoy from Mr Briney

3:17 am, stay posted for future me please!

Thanks for your patience!

[image description: a digital illustration of Mr Briney’s motor boat speeding through the ocean with a nekomimi girl and espeon on board. Mr Briney is waving to Peeko (a wingull) from the back of the boat. The girl and espeon are at the front, leaning into the wind. The main hue is salmon-orange.]

Comments under the cut!

I was pretty pumped for this one while working on it but I tripped up a bit at the final colouring. It’s not terrible or anything, I still rather like it, but the colour sketch had a little more impact that got lost in translation. I don’t think I’ve ever drawn a boat before. Even though it was a struggle, I’m pretty pleased with the result :)

summary:
If
 the player manages to fill their party and all boxes before the Old Man
 capture demonstration in Japanese versions of...
caption: If the player manages to fill their party and all boxes before the Old Man capture demonstration in Japanese versions of Pokemon Red, Green, and Blue, the game will enter a soft locked state as the Old Man throws the Pokeball, encounters the full box message, and throws the Pokeball again in an infinite loop. This oversight was fixed in Japanese versions of Pokemon Yellow as well as all localizations of Red and Blue.

summary:
Graylian- the extra terrestrial pokemon
(Genderless)
Type: psychic | ability: anti grav (levitate but it effects all pokemon on...
body:
Graylian- the extra terrestrial pokemon

(Genderless)

Type: psychic | ability: anti grav (levitate but it effects all pokemon on the field making ground moves useless)

This pokemon was found in the desert one day and since then it has multiplied in numbers. These pokemon are tenderness but somehow more and more keep popping up without any evidence from as to where. No one knows where in the cosmos it came from but it stares longingly up into the sky every night.

*evolves at level 20*

Yuephoe- the flying saucer pokemon.

Type: psychic/steel | Ability: anti grav

This pokemon came about after several graylian stood outside and sent strange waves into the night sky. The next day Yuephoe was just there. It can generate a shockwave that renders the gravity in any enclosed area null and void.

*evolves at level 40*

Cryptalian- the mothership pokemon

Type: psychic/steel | ability: anti grav

After four Yuephoe were found in the wild, they all convened in the same place the first graylian was found. The next morning cryptalian had arrived. It had the ability to control the minds of the graylian and Yuephoe. Whenever it lifts its “skirt” another graylian pops out.

New move: otherworldly beam

Type: ??? (Special)

Power: 80

Accuracy: 80%

Added effects: 100% super effective (2×)

Fun fact: graylian is only 4 inches tall and ways 0.1 pound. They are absolutely tiny.

Fun fact: if you leave your party with only a member of this line, and a bunch of extra pokeballs, the extra spaces will get filled with lv. 1 graylian. (Not all at once but like every 100 steps)

summary: Due to an anomaly in its damage formula, the move Present is capable of dealing abnormally high or abnormally low amounts of...
caption: Due to an anomaly in its damage formula, the move Present is capable of dealing abnormally high or abnormally low amounts of damage based on the typing of the defending Pokemon. This anomaly was only present in Pokemon Gold, Silver, and Stadium, but can be reproduced in Crystal and Stadium 2 if it is used in a link battle with any of the affected games.
